      "title": "Sri Lanka expects IMF staff level deal by August",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka is expecting a staff level agreement with the International Monetary Fund by August 2022, after a financial advisors work out a debt restructuring plan Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe said.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s inflation will top 60 percent and gross domestic product may shrink to 76 billion US dollars from 84 billion in 2018, he said.",
        "Sri Lanka will take up to 2025 to come back to old level he said.",
        "The steep depreciation has halved the real value of the Employees Provident Fund has halved and older people will suffer, he said.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s debt to GDP ratio has grown to 140 percent of GDP he said."
      ],
